Tab to transient is a feature in Pro Tools that allows you to "jump" to the peak areas ([[transient]]s) of an [[audio]] file.

You need to first enable the '''Tab To Transient''' feature. Do this by clicking the Tab To Transient button so that it is blue (image below)





[[File:Pro Tools tab to transient button .png]]






'''1.''' Use the [[Pro_Tools:Tools#Selector_Tool|selector tool]] and place the cursor on the audio region.

'''2.''' Push '''Tab'''.

To go in the reverse direction hold down '''Option''' and push '''Tab'''

====To select  region by transient==== 

'''1.''' Use the selector tool and place the cursor on the audio region.

'''2.''' Hold '''Shift''' and push '''Tab'''


To select the reverse: 

Hold '''Shift''' and '''Option''' at the same time and then push '''Tab'''




